trans-unit.source:
Every medical expert on HealthTap has a DocScore. This is a reputation score from 0 to 5 stars that reflects the peer-recognition that this doctor has received on HealthTap as well as relevant public information about this expert, including: • Agrees, votes, and recommendations from other doctors • Years of experience
• Quality of experts who refer to them
• Where the expert studied and trained
• Board certification(s)
• Other professional accomplishments (such as peer reviewed publications and awards) • Thanks, votes, and recommendations from members
trans-unit.target:
Cada médico experto en HealthTap tiene una DocScore. Este es un puntaje de reputación desde 0 a 5 estrellas que refleja el reconocimiento de los colegas que este ha recibido en HealthTap, así como también información pública relevante acerca de este experto, incluyendo: • Acuerdos, votos y recomendaciones de otros médicos • Años de experiencia
• Calidad de los expertos que los refieran
• Dónde estudiaron y se entrenaron los expertos
• Certificado(s) del Consejo
• Otros logros profesionales (tales como publicaciones y premios revisados por sus colegas) • Agradecimientos, votos, y recomendaciones de los miembros

• Years of experience

• Quality of experts who refer to them

• Where the expert studied and trained

• Board certification(s)

• Other professional accomplishments (such as peer reviewed publications and awards) • Thanks, votes, and recommendations from members"; ObjectID = "dSG-zo-7RR";

trans-unit.source: We safeguard your payment information with SSL (Secure Sockets Layer) when sent over the Internet. SSL encrypts personal information, including your name and payment information, so that it cannot be read in transit by a third party. We also store your payment information in an encrypted format.
trans-unit.target: Salvaguardamos tu información de pago con SSL (Secure Sockets Layer) cuando es enviada por Internet. SSL cifra la información personal, incluyendo tu nombre e información de pago, para que no pueda ser leída en tránsito por un tercero. También almacenamos tu información de pago en un formato cifrado.

trans-unit.source:
Every medical expert on HealthTap has a DocScore. This is a reputation score from 0 to 5 stars that reflects the peer-recognition that this doctor has received on HealthTap as well as relevant public information about this expert, including: • Agrees, votes, and recommendations from other doctors • Years of experience
• Quality of experts who refer to them
• Where the expert studied and trained
• Board certification(s)
• Other professional accomplishments (such as peer reviewed publications and awards) • Thanks, votes, and recommendations from members
trans-unit.target:
Cada médico experto en HealthTap tiene una DocScore. Este es un puntaje de reputación desde 0 a 5 estrellas que refleja el reconocimiento de los colegas que este ha recibido en HealthTap, así como también información pública relevante acerca de este experto, incluyendo: • Acuerdos, votos y recomendaciones de otros médicos • Años de experiencia
• Calidad de los expertos que los refieran
• Dónde estudiaron y se entrenaron los expertos
• Certificado(s) del Consejo
• Otros logros profesionales (tales como publicaciones y premios revisados por sus colegas) • Agradecimientos, votos, y recomendaciones de los miembros
trans-unit.note:

trans-unit.id: Common reasons to use Virtual Consults
trans-unit.resname: Common reasons to use Virtual Consults
trans-unit.source: Common reasons to use Virtual Consults
trans-unit.target: Razones comunes para usar Consultas Virtuales

trans-unit.id:
Common reasons to use Virtual Consults

 · Abdominal Pain

 · Acute Bronchitis

 · Acute Conjunctivistis

 · Acute Cystitis



 When not to use Virtual Consults


 Always call %@ or your local emergency service immediately if you think you have an emergency. For example, if you experience any of the following medical issues, go immediately to an %@:


 · Chest pain or pressure

 · Convulsions or seizures

 · Difficulty breathing

 · Mental health / behavioral health / addiction issues

 · Moderate to severe burns

 · Pain medication (narcotics)

 · Poisoning

 · Serious head, neck, or back injury

 · Serious limb impairment or broken bone(s)

 · Significant, uncontrolled bleeding

 · Suicide ideation

 · Unconsciousness

 · Any other critical or life-threatening situation


 What not to expect


 · Any prescription for narcotics or DEA (Drug Enforcement Administration) controlled substances (Schedule I, II, III, IV)

 · Any prescriptions for medications that are restricted by individual states

 · Any prescriptions for psychiatric or lifestyle medications (for example, diet or erectile dysfunction drugs)

 · Consults in languages other than English

 · Instant responses to inbox / message consults (consider video consults with available doctors for faster care)

Por ejemplo, si experimentas cualquiera de los siguientes problemas médicos, dirígete inmediatamente a un %2$@: · Dolor de pecho o presión en el pecho · Convulsiones · Dificultad al respirar · Problemas de salud mental / salud conductual / adicción · Quemaduras moderadas a severas · Medicamento para el dolor (narcóticos) · Envenenamiento · Lesión grave en la cabeza, cuello o espalda · Disfunción grave de extremidades o hueso(s) roto(s) · Hemorragia significativa no controlada · Ideación suicida · Pérdida del conocimiento · Cualquier otra situación crítica o que atente contra la vida Qué no debe esperarse · Ninguna receta para narcóticos o para sustancias controladas por la DEA (Drug Enforcement Administration, Agencia Federal Antidrogas) (Programa I, II, III, IV) · Cualquier receta para medicamentos que sean restringidos por distintos estados · Cualquier receta para medicamentos psiquiátricos o para el estilo de vida (por ejemplo, fármacos para dietas o para disfunción eréctil) · Consultas en idiomas que no sea el inglés · Respuestas inmediatas a consultas buzón de entrada / mensajes (considera consultas en video con doctores disponibles para una atención más rápida)

trans-unit.source:
You've talked to a doctor X times this month. Remember, HealthTap Virtual Consults are not meant to replace your primary care physician or be used as a substitute for establishing a relationship with a doctor in the real world.
We'd like you to contact us at [support@healthtap.com] to let us know why you need to continue talking to a doctor. We'd be happy to review your case and, if appropriate, enable you to start another consult. We're here to help!
trans-unit.target:
Has hablado con un doctor X veces este mes. Recuerda, las Consultas Virtuales de HealthTap no pretenden reemplazar a tu doctor de atención primaria o utilizarse como sustituto para establecer una relación con un doctor en el mundo real.
Nos gustaría que te comunicaras con nosotros al [support@healthtap.com] para hacernos saber la razón por la que necesita continuar hablando con un doctor. Estaremos felices de revisar tu caso y, si es apropiado, permitirte comenzar otra consulta. ¡Estamos aquí para ayudar!

trans-unit.source:
Every medical expert on HealthTap has a DocScore. This is a reputation score from 0 to 5 stars that reflects the peer-recognition that this doctor has received on HealthTap as well as relevant public information about this expert, including: • Agrees, votes, and recommendations from other doctors • Years of experience
• Quality of experts who refer to them
• Where the expert studied and trained
• Board certification(s)
• Other professional accomplishments (such as peer reviewed publications and awards) • Thanks, votes, and recommendations from members
trans-unit.target: HealthTap上的每位医学专家都有一个DocScore。这个评分系统从0到5星，反映了这名医生在HealthTap上的认可度以及这位专业医生相关的公开信息，包括： 其他医生的赞同、投票和推荐 从业时间 与其相关的专家水平 学业技能学习履历 学会认证证书 其他学术成就（如同业审评论文和奖项） 成员的感谢、投票和推荐

trans-unit.source: We safeguard your payment information with SSL (Secure Sockets Layer) when sent over the Internet. SSL encrypts personal information, including your name and payment information, so that it cannot be read in transit by a third party. We also store your payment information in an encrypted format.

trans-unit.source:
Every medical expert on HealthTap has a DocScore. This is a reputation score from 0 to 5 stars that reflects the peer-recognition that this doctor has received on HealthTap as well as relevant public information about this expert, including: • Agrees, votes, and recommendations from other doctors • Years of experience
• Quality of experts who refer to them
• Where the expert studied and trained
• Board certification(s)
• Other professional accomplishments (such as peer reviewed publications and awards) • Thanks, votes, and recommendations from members

trans-unit.id:
Common reasons to use Virtual Consults

 · Abdominal Pain

 · Acute Bronchitis

 · Acute Conjunctivistis

 · Acute Cystitis



 When not to use Virtual Consults


 Always call %@ or your local emergency service immediately if you think you have an emergency. For example, if you experience any of the following medical issues, go immediately to an %@:


 · Chest pain or pressure

 · Convulsions or seizures

 · Difficulty breathing

 · Mental health / behavioral health / addiction issues

 · Moderate to severe burns

 · Pain medication (narcotics)

 · Poisoning

 · Serious head, neck, or back injury

 · Serious limb impairment or broken bone(s)

 · Significant, uncontrolled bleeding

 · Suicide ideation

 · Unconsciousness

 · Any other critical or life-threatening situation


 What not to expect


 · Any prescription for narcotics or DEA (Drug Enforcement Administration) controlled substances (Schedule I, II, III, IV)

 · Any prescriptions for medications that are restricted by individual states

 · Any prescriptions for psychiatric or lifestyle medications (for example, diet or erectile dysfunction drugs)

 · Consults in languages other than English

 · Instant responses to inbox / message consults (consider video consults with available doctors for faster care)

\n When not to use Virtual Consults

\n Always call %@ or your local emergency service immediately if you think you have an emergency. For example, if you experience any of the following medical issues, go immediately to an %@:

\n · Chest pain or pressure
\n · Convulsions or seizures
\n · Difficulty breathing
\n · Mental health / behavioral health / addiction issues
\n · Moderate to severe burns
\n · Pain medication (narcotics)
\n · Poisoning
\n · Serious head, neck, or back injury
\n · Serious limb impairment or broken bone(s)
\n · Significant, uncontrolled bleeding
\n · Suicide ideation
\n · Unconsciousness
\n · Any other critical or life-threatening situation

\n What not to expect

\n · Any prescription for narcotics or DEA (Drug Enforcement Administration) controlled substances (Schedule I, II, III, IV)
\n · Any prescriptions for medications that are restricted by individual states
\n · Any prescriptions for psychiatric or lifestyle medications (for example, diet or erectile dysfunction drugs)
\n · Consults in languages other than English
\n · Instant responses to inbox / message consults (consider video consults with available doctors for faster care)

\ Cuándo no usar Consultas Virtuales

\ Siempre llama al %@ o a tu servicio local de emergencia inmediatamente si crees que tienes una emergencia. Por ejemplo, si experimentas cualquiera de los siguientes problemas médicos, ve inmediatamente a un %@:

\ · Dolor o presión en pecho
\ · Convulsiones
\ · Dificultad para respirar
\ · Problemas de salud mental / salud conductual / adicción
\ · Quemaduras moderadas a severas

\ · Envenenamiento

\n When not to use Virtual Consults

\n Always call %@ or your local emergency service immediately if you think you have an emergency. For example, if you experience any of the following medical issues, go immediately to an %@:

\n · Chest pain or pressure
\n · Convulsions or seizures
\n · Difficulty breathing
\n · Mental health / behavioral health / addiction issues
\n · Moderate to severe burns
\n · Pain medication (narcotics)
\n · Poisoning
\n · Serious head, neck, or back injury
\n · Serious limb impairment or broken bone(s)
\n · Significant, uncontrolled bleeding
\n · Suicide ideation
\n · Unconsciousness
\n · Any other critical or life-threatening situation

\n What not to expect

\n · Any prescription for narcotics or DEA (Drug Enforcement Administration) controlled substances (Schedule I, II, III, IV)
\n · Any prescriptions for medications that are restricted by individual states
\n · Any prescriptions for psychiatric or lifestyle medications (for example, diet or erectile dysfunction drugs)
\n · Consults in languages other than English
\n · Instant responses to inbox / message consults (consider video consults with available doctors for faster care)

Every medical expert on HealthTap has a DocScore. This is a reputation score from 0 to 5 stars that reflects the peer-recognition that this doctor has received on HealthTap as well as relevant public information about this expert, including: • Agrees, votes, and recommendations from other doctors 
• Years of experience

• Quality of experts who refer to them

• Where the expert studied and trained

• Board certification(s)

• Other professional accomplishments (such as peer reviewed publications and awards) • Thanks, votes, and recommendations from members

• Años de experiencia

• Calidad de los expertos que los refieren

• Dónde estudió y entrenó el experto

• Certificación(es) por Consejo

• Otros logros profesionales (como publicaciones con revisión por pares y galardones) • Agradecimientos, votos y recomendaciones de otros miembros

\n When not to use Virtual Consults

\n Always call %@ or your local emergency service immediately if you think you have an emergency. For example, if you experience any of the following medical issues, go immediately to an %@:

\n · Chest pain or pressure
\n · Convulsions or seizures
\n · Difficulty breathing
\n · Mental health / behavioral health / addiction issues
\n · Moderate to severe burns
\n · Pain medication (narcotics)
\n · Poisoning
\n · Serious head, neck, or back injury
\n · Serious limb impairment or broken bone(s)
\n · Significant, uncontrolled bleeding
\n · Suicide ideation
\n · Unconsciousness
\n · Any other critical or life-threatening situation

\n What not to expect

\n · Any prescription for narcotics or DEA (Drug Enforcement Administration) controlled substances (Schedule I, II, III, IV)
\n · Any prescriptions for medications that are restricted by individual states
\n · Any prescriptions for psychiatric or lifestyle medications (for example, diet or erectile dysfunction drugs)
\n · Consults in languages other than English
\n · Instant responses to inbox / message consults (consider video consults with available doctors for faster care)
